--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Prior art that shaped the design
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

JobSpy
  https://github.com/speedyapply/JobSpy
  Multi-board scraping across Indeed, LinkedIn, Glassdoor, ZipRecruiter and
  Google. Used through the `python-jobspy` package as an optional source
  adapter, installed only via the `jobspy` extra. Not vendored; no code copied.

DevJobsHub
  https://github.com/pranavv00/devjobs.site
  The remote-first aggregation pattern over WeWorkRemotely, Remotive, RemoteOK
  and WorkingNomads, and the general shape of HTML cleaning and relative-date
  parsing. Independently reimplemented here; no code copied.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Data sources
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Postings are retrieved at runtime from the public APIs and feeds listed below.
This project redistributes none of their data; it fetches on the user's own
machine, for that user's own use. Each service's terms of use apply to whoever
runs the engine, and adapters are written to be polite (rate limiting, backoff
on HTTP 429, bounded pagination).

  Himalayas        https://himalayas.app
  Remotive         https://remotive.com
  RemoteOK         https://remoteok.com
  WeWorkRemotely   https://weworkremotely.com
  WorkingNomads    https://www.workingnomads.com

Job posting content retrieved from these services remains the property of its
respective owners.
